import React from 'react'
import { Image, Divider, Dropdown, } from 'semantic-ui-react'
import iunnologo from '../Assets/iunnologo.png'
import { NavLink } from 'react-router-dom'

export default class Header extends React.Component {

    render() {

        return (
            <>
                <center>
                    <Divider hidden/>
                    <NavLink to='/'><Image src={iunnologo} /></NavLink>
                    <Divider hidden/>
                    {/* <Divider hidden/> */}
                    <Sidebar.Pushable as={Segment}>
      <Sidebar
        as={Menu}
        animation='overlay'
        icon='labeled'
        inverted
        onHide={() => setVisible(false)}
        vertical
        visible={visible}
        width='thin'
      >
        <Menu.Item as='a'>
          <Icon name='home' />
          Home
        </Menu.Item>
        <Menu.Item as='a'>
          <Icon name='gamepad' />
          Games
        </Menu.Item>
        <Menu.Item as='a'>
          <Icon name='camera' />
          Channels
        </Menu.Item>
      </Sidebar>

      <Sidebar.Pusher dimmed={visible}>
        <Segment basic>
          <Header as='h3'>Application Content</Header>
          <Image src='https://react.semantic-ui.com/images/wireframe/paragraph.png' />
        </Segment>
      </Sidebar.Pusher>
    </Sidebar.Pushable>
                    <Dropdown basic icon='align justify' floating   className='icon'>
                        <Dropdown.Menu>
                            <Dropdown.Item text='Cancel Order' />
                            <NavLink to='/history'> <Dropdown.Item text='View Order History' /> </NavLink>
                            <NavLink to='/profile'> <Dropdown.Item text='Edit Profile'/> </NavLink>
                            <NavLink to='/'> <Dropdown.Item signOut={() => this.props.signOut()} text='Sign Out'/> </NavLink>
                        </Dropdown.Menu>
                    </Dropdown>
                </center>
                

        </>

        )
    }

}
